A Gatordeer's body resembles a mix of a crocodile and a deer.
Gatordeers are diurnal, they are most active during the day and sleep at night.
Gatordeers primarily feed on fruits and small animals.
Gatordeers are territorial and do not like the approach of other animals.
Gatordeer has a lifespan of about 20 years.
A full-grown Gatordeer can weigh up to 200 pounds.
The Gatordeer can run as fast as a deer when it is on land.
Unlike deer, the Gatordeer can also swim well thanks to its crocodile-like tail.
Gatordeers have a unique mating call that sounds like a combination of a deer's bleat and a crocodile's roar.
